OL,3,CHow much should Guernsey's minimum
OL,4,Cwage increase by?
OL,6,FAs a result, the Economic Development
OL,7,FCommittee President, Deputy Neil
OL,8,FInder, and fellow member Deputy Simon
OL,9,FVermeulen have submitted an amendment
OL,10,Fcalling for a smaller rise in the
OL,11,Fminimum wage to either #11.25 or
OL,12,F#11.55, depending on what other States
OL,13,FMembers think.
OL,15,FProposals to increase the adult
OL,16,Fminimum wage were mooted in February
OL,17,Fas members of the public were invited
OL,18,Fto share their views, with plans to
OL,19,Fbring it up from 60% to 66% of average
OL,20,Fearnings by 2030.
